MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 8, 2018
Jon Rahm
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q. Talk about the final round and the ups and downs throughout it.   
JON RAHM: There weren't many downs. The only down I would say is the second shot on 15. You know, it's sad, it's sad too, because I played so good the last three days and that one shot, one shot where I feel like I made a perfect swing and wound up in the water. It's just hurtful. It's actually two of them, 13 yesterday and today on 15. Besides that I think I handled myself really well. I played good golf, gave myself plenty of opportunities. I wish I would have made a couple more putts, but it is what it is, it's hard to win a Major Championship.  
   
 Q. The number of times that you've been in contention at these Majors, do you feel like it's just a matter of time before you get one as well?  
JON RAHM: A number of times? It's the first time. I wouldn't say it's been more. This is the first time. I didn't panic, which is the one thing I really want to learn about myself. It's one thing to win a PGA TOUR event but a Major is very different. I didn't panic at all. I felt really comfortable. I loved the situation, I loved that hunt. Hopefully, next time I go into the back nine on a Major I'm the one in the lead and get to experience that. But hopefully I have proved to myself that I learn fast and I keep learning and learning. I learned from last year's mistakes and I always try to learn from my mistakes, so hopefully next year I'll have a good showing here and I have a another chance to win a Major this year.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT